        "cooked": "<p><strong>2017 Cecile Tremblay Morey St. Denis Tres Girard</strong> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Morey St. Denis (1/3/2020)</em></p>\n<p>Expressive black fruit, cassis and truffle followed by a fine, supple palate with a lovely core of cool fruit and juicy tannins. Elegant and refined a very charming MSD !! <em><strong>(92 pts.)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
