      {
        "id": 2784763,
        "name": "Barry Rothof",
        "username": "Barry_Rothof",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/barry_rothof/{size}/1215_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-04T22:18:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"157293\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"157293\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"157293\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Nice note. Soon this cuv\u00e9e will get a big bigger when some vines that are in fermage revert to her.</p>\n<p>Just writing up my tasting of her 2018s, coincidentally!</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>There was also a 2017 Cecile Tremblay Bourgogne C\u00f4te d\u2019Or on the winelist! A new cuv\u00e9e?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I can answer that! This used to be the Bourgogne cuv\u00e9e \u201cCroix Blanche\u201d, which came from the lieu dit of that name in Vosne-Roman\u00e9e (one of the superior regional spots in the commune). But C\u00e9cile then got some Bourgogne in the commune of Chambolle-Musigny, so the name didn\u2019t make sense. Her partner Philippe Charlopin was also one of the cheerleaders for the new \u201cBourgogne C\u00f4te d\u2019Or\u201d AOC as I understand it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thanks William, will try this cuv\u00e9e soon!</p>",
